/dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Men's_Basketball_Tournament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This summer, the U.S. women's basketball team is expected to pursue its eighth consecutive Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans have won 55 straight games in Olympic play and are favored to continue that streak in Paris.\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.326774167152859e-27, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 2786, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the official roster has not yet been announced,Diana Taurasi(Chino, California), who will be 42 years old when the 2024 Games begin, has said that Paris is \\\"on my radar.\\\"\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diana Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}, {\"begin\": 2860, \"end\": 2877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chino, California\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\"}, {\"begin\": 2860, \"end\": 2877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chino, California\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino,_California\"}, {\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Getty Images  The U.S. women are favorites to win gold in Paris but they have not done so since the 2012 Olympics in London.\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3029, \"end\": 3034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3088, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1032482359138226e-14, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because playersMegan Rapinoe,Julie ErtzandAli Kriegerhave retired, you can expect to see up-and-coming stars such asNaomi Girma(San Jose, California),Sophia Smith(Windsor, Colorado) andAlyssa Thompson(Studio City, California) step up as the U.S. looks to bounce back from the team's worst-ever showing at the World Cup in 2023 (eliminated in Round of 16).\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3288, \"end\": 3296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999998017729209, \"rank\": 1.982267755301896e-07, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Studio City, California\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Studio City, California\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_City,_Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sha'Carri Richardsonis poised to bring her signature style and flair to Paris this summer.\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3525, \"end\": 3530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She'd enter the Paris Olympics as the reigning 100m world champion after her win in Budapest, Hungary in 2023, where she also took home bronze in the 200m and gold in the 4x100m, anchoring the U.S. to the world title.\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1075373379679614e-17, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}, {\"begin\": 3638, \"end\": 3645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.6545448803589885, \"rank\": 0.5277791179904205, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A common refrain for Richardson over the last several years: \\\"I am not back.\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3783, \"end\": 3793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2548770258764454e-14, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am better.\\\"\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris would mark the Dallas native's Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3874, \"end\": 3880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"score\": 0.9988340626568076, \"rank\": 0.0008803207962256462, \"text\": \"Dallas\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At just 24 years old (she will turn 25 during the Olympics),Sydney McLaughlin-Levronehas made a habit ofbreaking records.\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 4027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When she was 17, McLaughlin-Levrone made her Olympic debut in Rio, becoming the youngest member of the U.S. Track and Field team to compete at the Olympics since 1972.\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4090, \"end\": 4093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4837655606073343e-38, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, she has made history in her signature event, the 400m hurdles, in which she broke the world record four times in a span of 13 months.\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track star might shift focus to the flat 400m in Paris, or look to continue her dominance in the 400m hurdles (or, perhaps, attempt an audacious double).\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4395, \"end\": 4400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anna Hallis expected to make her long-awaited debut on the Olympic stage this summer in Paris.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4501, \"end\": 4505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"score\": 0.9999405985844584, \"rank\": 5.258031144043215e-05, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\"}, {\"begin\": 4589, \"end\": 4594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall crashed out of the 100m hurdles event of the heptathlon at the U.S. Olympic Trials for Tokyo, which led to a foot injury that required surgery, forcing her to miss the Games.\", \"from\": 4596, \"to\": 4775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, Hall has the chance to joinJackie Joyner-Kerseeas the only American woman to win Olympic gold in the heptathlon.\", \"from\": 4776, \"to\": 4898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4779, \"end\": 4784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4845, \"end\": 4859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0846273469864288e-31, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track starShelly-Ann Fraser-Pryceis expected to appear in her fifth Olympic games in Paris.\", \"from\": 4900, \"to\": 4991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4985, \"end\": 4990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She made history in Beijing in 2008 as the first woman from the Caribbean to win gold in the 100m.\", \"from\": 4992, \"to\": 5090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5012, \"end\": 5019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7277843501126207e-45, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout herOlympic journey, Fraser-Pryce became the first 100-meter sprinter to win individual medals in four consecutive Olympic games and has won eight medals total on the Olympic stage.\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is expected to be her final run at the Olympics before she retires from the sport that she has dominated for so long.\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5283, \"end\": 5288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carl Davaz/For The Register-Guard / USA TODAY NETWORK  Faith Kipyegonfirst turned heads when she pulled off a major upset against Ethiopia'sGenzebe Dibabato win 1500m gold at the 2016 Rio Olympics.\", \"from\": 5408, \"to\": 5605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5423, \"end\": 5441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Register-Guard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Register-Guard\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Register-Guard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Register-Guard\"}, {\"begin\": 5444, \"end\": 5461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA TODAY NETWORK\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\"}, {\"begin\": 5444, \"end\": 5461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA TODAY NETWORK\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\"}, {\"begin\": 5538, \"end\": 5546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9437463265013092, \"rank\": 0.05960677346816448, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, she has established herself as thebest 1500m runner in the worldand she is the current world record holder in both the 1500m and mile, as well as the former world record holder in the 5000m.\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In pursuit of more history, Kipyegon has said that she hopes to become the first Kenyan athlete to earn Olympic gold in three consecutive Games when she competes in Paris this summer.\", \"from\": 5809, \"to\": 5992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5974, \"end\": 5979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indianapolis Star-USA TODAY Sports  History's greatest female distance swimmer will look to continue her dominance at her fourth Olympics in Paris.Katie Ledeckyenters Paris a gold medal favorite in multiple events, including the 800m and 1500m freestyle.\", \"from\": 5994, \"to\": 6248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5994, \"end\": 6006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999998574676384, \"rank\": 9.222423800874738e-08, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}, {\"begin\": 6016, \"end\": 6021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Today\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.238743892775872e-31, \"text\": \"TODAY\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Today\"}, {\"begin\": 6161, \"end\": 6166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bethesda, Maryland native needs just three more gold medals to bring her total up to 10 on the Olympic stage.\", \"from\": 6249, \"to\": 6362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With 10 career Olympic gold medals, Ledecky would be second all-time in any sport only toMichael Phelps.\", \"from\": 6363, \"to\": 6467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning three more medals of any color would make her the most decorated U.S. woman in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 6468, \"to\": 6571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Getty Images  Ariarne Titmusis one of Ledecky's fiercest challengers.\", \"from\": 6573, \"to\": 6642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is the defending Olympic champion in the 200m free and 400m free, and set a new world record in the 400m freestyle at the 2023 World Championships.\", \"from\": 6643, \"to\": 6794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus and Ledecky are expected to go head-to-head once again on the Paris stage.\", \"from\": 6795, \"to\": 6876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6795, \"end\": 6801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 6864, \"end\": 6869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5254184417188327e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Getty Images  At just 17 years old,Summer McIntoshhas quickly taken the swimming world by storm.\", \"from\": 6878, \"to\": 6974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6878, \"end\": 6883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999755252750363, \"rank\": 2.4474497043636707e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the daughter of former Canadian Olympic team swimmerJill Horstead, McIntosh has certainly followed in her mother's footsteps.\", \"from\": 6975, \"to\": 7103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7001, \"end\": 7022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.791724952906979e-11, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7045, \"end\": 7053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.353934131434342e-17, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is a four-time world champion and currently holds the word record in the women's 400m individual medley.\", \"from\": 7104, \"to\": 7212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Be prepared for her to contend for multiple gold medals and be competitive against Ledecky and Titmus,especially in the 400m free.\", \"from\": 7213, \"to\": 7343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7308, \"end\": 7314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Getty Images  Kate Douglasswas a force to be reckoned with at the collegiate level, graduating from the University of Virginia in 2023 with 15 NCAA title